BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:The full moon closest to the Summer Solstice (for those of y
 ou in the Northern Hemisphere) is known as the Mead Moon. In ancient tra
 ditions\, drinking mead under the 'Mead Moon' would promote healing\, fe
 rtility and prosperity throughout the year. So let's crack open a bottle
  of honey wine!\n\nOf course we'll be drinking blue mead because when yo
 u've got two full moons in a single calendar month\, the second one is a
  'blue moon'...
DTEND:20260531T084507Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20260531T084507Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T230800Z
SUMMARY:🌕 Full Moon (Blue Mead)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
