BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250101T010013Z
DESCRIPTION:The waxing gibbous moon will set around midnight\, so watch 
 for meteors just midnight through the wee hours of dawn.\n\nThese fast-m
 oving meteors sometimes produce bright fireballs\, which might be able t
 o overcome a moonlit glare. If you trace these meteors backward\, they s
 eem to radiate from the Club of the famous constellation Orion the Hunte
 r.\n\nThe Orionids is produced by dust grains left behind by comet Halle
 y\, which has been known and observed since ancient times.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261023
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261021
LAST-MODIFIED:20260101T032947Z
SUMMARY:Orionids Meteor Shower
