BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20241002T193042Z
DESCRIPTION:The Apophis asteroid will pass less than 20\,000 miles (32\,
 000 kilometers) from our planet's surface – closer than the distance of 
 geosynchronous satellites. During the approach\, Apophis should be visib
 le to observers in the Eastern Hemisphere with a brightness magnitude of
  3.1 -- no need for a telescope or binoculars. The asteroid is 370 meter
 s wide. Were it to impact Earth\, it would hit with 1200 megatons of for
 ce leaving a 5km impact crater.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20290414
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20290413
LAST-MODIFIED:20241002T193752Z
SUMMARY:Apophis Asteroid Fly-By
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0062-20251231-223152-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
END:VEVENT
