BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Brr! The December full moon is also known as the Ice Moon\, 
 Snow Moon\, Long Nights Moon\, and my very favorite (from the Cree)\, Fr
 ost Exploding Trees Moon.\n\n"We saw 47 below on our porch\, and we didn
 't look again. I would hear these bangs and I blamed it on the house exp
 anding or contracting\, or whatever\, from the cold\, but it was the tre
 es exploding. It was the bark bursting\, and you could hear it. That's h
 ow wild it was."\n— Shirley Loudon
DTEND:20261224T012809Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20261224T012809Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T232006Z
SUMMARY:🌕 Super Full Moon (Bitter)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0065-20251231-223152-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exploding_tree
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:In the northern hemisphere\, this marks the first day of sum
 mer and is the day with most hours of light in the year -- when the Sun 
 is farthest north. In the southern hemisphere\, this is your winter sols
 tice\, marking the shortest day of the year.
DTEND:20270621T141050Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20270621T141050Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T224143Z
SUMMARY:June Solstice
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0066-20251231-223152-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250103T133110Z
DESCRIPTION:To experience greatest totality\, you might get a lucky brea
 k in the clouds in Greenland or Iceland... but unlikely according to Ecl
 ipsophile:\n\n"Two-thirds of the Moon’s shadow path falls over water and
  even a casual glance at Figure 1 shows that ship-borne viewing sites wi
 ll be challenged to find good weather. Instead\, the best observing site
 s are on land or close to land and of these\, Spain and Mallorca are the
  most promising."
DTEND:20260812T195700Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20260812T153400Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250103T133137Z
SUMMARY:Total Solar Eclipse (Spain and Mallorca)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0067-20251231-223152-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://eclipsophile.com/tse2026/
