BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250101T003708Z
DESCRIPTION:"Earth at Aphelion" refers to the point in Earth's orbit whe
 re it is farthest from the Sun\, a phenomenon that occurs annually. This
  coincides very nearly with winter solstice in the Southern Hemisphere\,
  leading to especially cold temperatures there due to the combined effec
 t of Earth's axial tilt away from the Sun and the increased orbital dist
 ance. Brr!
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260707
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260706
