BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:The term "Sturgeon Moon" refers to the full moon in August a
 nd originates from Native American tribes in North America. They named i
 t after the sturgeon fish\, which was abundant and most easily caught in
  the Great Lakes and other major bodies of water during this time of the
  year.\n\nEver seen a sturgeon? Living dinosaurs! This fish species date
 s back to the Late Cretaceous period\, around 100 million years ago\, ma
 king them one of the oldest surviving fish species. Google yourself some
  'great lakes sturgeon' pictures. Weird looking\, but allegedly one of t
 he tastiest fish in the world. 
DTEND:20260828T041826Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20260828T041826Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T231214Z
SUMMARY:🌕 Full Moon (Sturgeon)
