BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:The Sun will beam down directly on the equator giving us jus
 t about equal amounts of day and night in most parts of the world. North
  of the equator\, this is your Autumnal Equinox. If you live south of th
 e equator\, this is your Spring Equinox.\n\nAlso\, try balancing an egg 
 on its end! Whether or not you succeed has nothing to do with the Equino
 x\, but it's still a fun game to try on any day of the year. :)
DTEND:20270923T060132Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20270923T060132Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T224113Z
SUMMARY:September Equinox
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0114-20251231-223153-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:The Farmer's Almanac described this as the Harvest Moon beca
 use it gave farmers several extra evenings of moonlight to allow them to
  finish their harvests before the frosts of fall arrived. Tender vegetab
 les such as tomatoes\, peppers\, winter squash\, and pumpkins must be pi
 cked before the first frost.\n\n"Come a little bit closer\nHear what I h
 ave to say\nJust like children sleepin'\nWe could dream this night away\
 nBut there's a full moon risin'\nLet's go dancin' in the light\nWe know 
 where the music's playin'\nLet's go out and feel the night\nBecause I'm 
 still in love with you\nI want to see you dance again\nBecause I'm still
  in love with you\nOn this harvest moon..."\n– Neil Young
DTEND:20260926T164857Z
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART:20260926T164857Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251231T231648Z
SUMMARY:🌕 Full Moon (Harvest)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0115-20251231-223153-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n2MtEsrcTTs
