BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250103T132119Z
DESCRIPTION:Just as North America experienced twice-in-a-lifetime solar 
 eclipses in 2017 and 2024\, on August 2nd 2027 Europe and Africa will ha
 ve their turn. \n\nThe eclipse will start in Morocco\, sweep across the 
 Mediterranean Sea\, and reach its peak totality in historic Luxor\, Egyp
 t. \n\nEclipsophile says\, "Cloud cover for this eclipse is among the lo
 west I’ve analyzed over the last 45 years... Just about anywhere will pr
 esent a good to excellent opportunity to see this event and bathe in ove
 r six minutes of totality."\nhttps://eclipsophile.com/tse2027/\n\nIf you
  live anywhere near the path of totality and have never seen a total ecl
 ipse of the sun\, DO NOT MISS THIS OPPORTUNITY.\n\nIf you live far away\
 , it's not too early to make travel plans. Many hotels in the path of to
 tality are already fully booked.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260802
LAST-MODIFIED:20260101T035044Z
SUMMARY:Reminder: Aug 2027 TOTAL Solar Eclipse
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0129-20251231-223153-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://eclipsophile.com/tse2027/
END:VEVENT
