BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250101T010752Z
DESCRIPTION:This year lands the Ursids right on top of the full moon. Gi
 ven that it's a minor shower... probably best just to get some sleep ton
 ight :)\n\nThe Ursids is a minor meteor shower producing about 5-10 mete
 ors per hour. It is produced by dust grains left behind by comet Tuttle\
 , which was first discovered in 1790. The shower runs annually from Dece
 mber 17-25. It peaks this year on the the night of the 21st and morning 
 of the 22nd. Meteors will radiate from the constellation Ursa Minor\, bu
 t can appear anywhere in the sky.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261223
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
