BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250101T003220Z
DESCRIPTION:"Earth at Perihelion" refers to the point in Earth's orbit w
 here it is nearest from the Sun\, a phenomenon that occurs annually. Dur
 ing perihelion\, Earth will be at its minimum distance from the Sun\, wh
 ich slightly intensifies the sunlight received but has a minimal impact 
 on global temperatures due to Earth's axial tilt\, which creates seasona
 l variations. This event coincides with winter in the Northern Hemispher
 e and summer in the Southern Hemisphere.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260104
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260103
LAST-MODIFIED:20260101T034317Z
SUMMARY:Earth at Perihelion
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0181-20251231-223153-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.timeanddate.com/astronomy/perihelion-aphelion-
 solstice.html
END:VEVENT
