BEGIN:VEVENT
CREATED:20250101T004950Z
DESCRIPTION:Whomp whomp. The full moon will outshine most of the meteors
  this year \n\nThe Delta Aquariid shower burns from around July 18 to Au
 gust 21. Shooting stars are rising in mid-evening\, up high around 2 a.m
 . and low in the sky by dawn.\n\nFavoring the Southern Hemisphere and tr
 opical Northern Hemisphere regions like the southern U.S.\, this shower 
 produces 15 to 20 meteors per hour. Originating from debris left by come
 ts Marsden and Kracht\, these meteors radiate near the star Skat in the 
 Aquarius constellation. Unlike many showers\, the Delta Aquarids don't h
 ave a sharp peak\, instead offering a steady display through late July a
 nd early August. During early August\, they often coincide with the Pers
 eids\, providing an enhanced experience\, particularly from southerly la
 titudes.
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260730
DTSTAMP:20260101T053147Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260728
LAST-MODIFIED:20260101T031455Z
SUMMARY:Delta Aquariid Meteor Shower
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:0184-20251231-223153-astrocal@cantonbecker.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://earthsky.org/astronomy-essentials/everything-you-n
 eed-to-know-delta-aquarid-meteor-shower/
END:VEVENT
